<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Has the busy effort to enscandal the Clinton
presidency finally reached the point where the only thing that
counts is the latest tweak in l'affaire Lewinsky or newest arcanum
shaken from the impenetrable muddle of ancient Whitewater and the
real business of the presidency is just time out? (Teepen, Cox News
Service) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ Whatever happened to our respect for love and
marriage, for religion and politics? It's outrageous the way we
disparage these righteous institutions, especially in the jokes we
tell. I submit the following as unconscionable examples. (Murray,
Cox News Service) MOVED MONDAY.
