<P>
   SKUBE-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ It will disappoint some people to learn
that Fats Waller played Bach. This would not surprise Gov. Zell
Miller. It is only his critics who would have trouble explaining
it. There have always been ignoramuses for whom classical music was
culturally defined. But now we find out it is racial as well,
something suited to this race but toxic to that one. (Skube,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN08 _ ON A MOUNTAINTOP SIX-MILES FROM A PAVED ROAD,
N.C. _ From the front porch there'll be a 140-degree view of at
least five mountain ranges and that's with clouds,' I babble into
the cell phone. ``I'm six miles up a gravel road from the nearest
pavement, and there are bears. Isn't that great?'' My son, back in
the flatlands of Columbus, Ohio, is not committing himself to an
answer. His silence is ominous, but I'm too excited to notice.
(Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
