</P>
<P>
   NEEDLES _ The pain of a shot could become a thing of the past as
Georgia researchers develop ways to inject medicine through the
skin without the use of traditional needles. From the development
of ``microneedles,'' several times smaller than the diameter of a
human hair, to a laser punch, the techniques would make it easier
for patients to get the drugs they need, reduce the chance of
infection and remove the need for medical workers to administer the
medications. (Lore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-LAKECHATUGE _ Lake Chatuge Adventure, in and around
Hiawassee, Ga., and a little mountain culture at the state historic
musical ``Reach of Song'' running through mid-August in Young
Harris. (Thrasher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). ETA: 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   MINOR-COLUMN08 _ It seemed to new parents Jim and Connie Brown
that their whole world might very well be spinning in a very
disorienting slow motion. They drove through the country, two-lane
roads in the northwest part of Siberia, away from the old wooden
cottages where who-knows-what had occurred. Away, away, away, as
the child in their arms, the stinking child with the deformed face,
screamed and cried and squirmed. And while this was the day they'd
been wanting, indeed, waiting for, the one thing they could not do
was bring themselves to look too long at the boy who was now their
son. (Minor, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
