   Afternoon Tea and Croquet matches are being held Tuesday,
Wednesday, and Thursday from 3 p.m. to 5 p.m. through August at the
Wequassett Inn in Chatham. Guests will play on the inn's croquet
lawn overlooking Pleasant Bay and feel if they are back in the days
of Jay Gatsby. Bed, Board and Bard is the offering of the Seven
Hills Inn in Lenox. The Tudor mansion, which just completed a
million dollar renovation, is offering a midweek package that
includes dining, accommodations, and theater with Shakespeare &AMP;
Company. Packages range from $99 to $163 a person for the overnight
package; additional nights are available. For information, call
800-869-6518. &QL; 
