<HEADER>
A3579 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS &LR;      07-07 0434
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HOFFMAN SHINES IN `WAG'; `AMISTAD' TOO SPIELBERG 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES:  &UR; ``Wag the Dog''  &LR; _ Dustin Hoffman is brilliant as
a producer charged with creating a fictional war to deflect
criticism of the president. His thinly disguised impersonation of
Robert Evans is as juicy as it gets. During some other historical
period the idea would seem preposterous, but not now. Robert De
Niro, in his best role in years, keeps this over-the-top comedy
from sailing off.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Amistad'' &LR;  _ Leave it to Steven Spielberg to make a movie
about slavery where the sun always seems to shine. He even turns a
sequence where slaves are drowning into an underwater ballet. And
it's all done to an excessive John Williams score. Where's the
agonizing pain? Sorry, that might hurt the box office.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``The Voyage of La Amistad'' &LR;  _ Narrated by Alfre Woodard, the
documentary is historically accurate and, ultimately, much more
horrifying than Spielberg's fictionalized version. Using drawings
and documents of the period, the filmmakers create a remarkable
portrait.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``The Replacement Killers'' &LR;  _ Chow Yun-Fat makes his American
debut with Mira Sorvino in an action drama where bullets speak
louder than words. Not half as good as John Woo's ``The Killer.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS:  &UR; July 7:  &LR; ``Good Will Hunting,'' ``The
Boxer,'' ``Six O'Clock News,'' ``Baby Monitor: Sound of Fear.''
 &UR; July 14:  &LR; ``Phantoms,'' ``The Winter Guest,'' ``Plato's Run,''
``Nil by Mouth,'' ``The Night Caller,'' ``The Call of the Wild: Dog
of the Yukon,'' ``French Exit,'' ``Swept From the Sea,''
``Illtown,'' ``Chairman of the Board.''  &UR; July 21:  &LR; ``Great
Expectations,'' ``Four Days in September,'' ``Krippendorf's
Tribe,'' ``Two Friends,'' ``The Education of Little Tree,''
``Kissing a Fool,'' ``Prince Valiant,'' ``Children of the Corn V:
Fields of Terror.''  &UR; July 28:  &LR; ``The Gingerbread Man,'' ``The
Peacekeeper,'' ``Paperback Romance,'' ``Dark City,'' ``A Kid in
Aladdin's Palace,'' ``Live Flesh.''  &UR; July 31:  &LR; ``Cousin
Cousine.'' &UR; Aug. 4:  &LR; ``Jackie Brown,'' ``Deceiver,'' ``Meet the
Deedles,'' ``Preston Sturges Collection,'' ``The Swan Princess
II.''  &UR; Aug. 11:  &LR; ``The Man in the Iron Mask,'' ``Senseless,''
``John and Julie,'' ``I Love You, I Love You Not,'' ``The Big
Lebowski,'' ``Hamsun,'' ``Merlin.''  &UR; Aug. 18:  &LR; ``The Apostle,''
``Kundun,'' ``An Alan Smithee Film: Burn Hollywood Burn,'' ``Summer
Fling,'' ``The Borrowers.''  &UR; Sept. 1:  &LR; ``Titanic.''  &UR; Sept. 15:
 &LR; ``Lady and the Tramp.''
</P>
</TEXT>
