   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-MINERS (Vorkuta, Russia) _ The worst thing about being a
miner in Russia's far north is that the while the miners go years
without pay, the mines are making their owners rich. By David
Filipov. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LIABILITY-GUNS (Washington) -- Legislation to exempt small
businesses from big product-liability damage awards would help some
gun manufacturers, especially the makers of Saturday Night
Specials. By Louise D. Palmer. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   OLIPHANT-COLUMN (Washington) _ Now, doubt cast on the Linda
Tripp ``talking points.'' By Thomas Oliphant. &UR;  &LR; (w and k coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MOXLEY-MURDER (Greenwich, Conn.) _ Twenty-three years after the
bloody murder of Martha Moxley, investigators are reopening the
case, probably hoping DNA typing can finally identify the killers.
