race, to the the owner of a Daytona fireworks company who laid off
100 workers because there was no Fourth of July celebration, the
fires have cost Florida hundreds of millions of dollars. But the
fires are just the most spectacular proof of a drought that is
damaging crops and hurting business all over the South. By Mireya
Navarro.
