   MASSACHUSETTS -- A study released Tuesday by a health care
watchdog group revealed that about 100,000 Massachusetts residents
are eligible for special Medicare benefits and are not receiving
them. President Clinton and local Massachusetts seniors'
organizations say increasing the awareness of eligible Social
Security recipients will become a priority. Preston
</P>
<P>
   NEVADA -- Most U.S. cities, including Las Vegas and Henderson,
are riding the wave of prosperity that is sweeping the nation,
according to a report released Tuesday by the National League of
Cities. But national city leaders, including the finance directors
for both Silver State cities, warn that the trend will not continue
and there will be a need to find other revenue sources in the
future. Preston
</P>
<P>
   NEW MEXICO -- BACA. Kathleen McGinty, President Clinton's top
