up support for buying the Baca Ranch. But that support appears to
be lacking in Congress, where funds to buy the 95,000-acre property
have been slashed. (Working.) Gorman
</P>
<P>
   OHIO -- DEWINE-TELECOMM. What does it mean for consumers when
telecommunications and entertainment companies merge? Will these
information empires lead to lower cable rates? Or higher phone
bills? Or more corporate evening news casts? The Senate
Subcommittee on Antitrust, Business Rights and Competition, chaired
by Ohio Republican Mike DeWine, held a hearing Tuesday to examine
the convergence and consolidation of telecommunications,
entertainment and information industries. Eckstein
</P>
<P>
   -- MEDICARE. Nearly 60 percent of low-income Ohioans eligible
for Medicare assistance are not receiving their benefits, according
to a study released Tuesday by a Washington-based consumer group.
Families USA criticizes federal and state governments for not
informing eligible recipients about the program, which subsidizes
Medicare premiums. Barton
</P>
<P>
   -- ROOFIES-DEWINE. (Working.) Sen. Mike DeWine has introduced a
bill to curb the nationwide proliferation of pharmaceutical drugs
among youth, like ``roofies,'' the so-called date-rape drug. Story
will also look at the impact of the drugs among Ohio teens. Egbert
</P>
<P>
   -- BOEHNER-LAWSUIT-STARR. (Working.) Comparing the allegation
that Independent Counsel Kenneth Starr illegally leaked information
to reporters WITH the claim Rep. Jim McDermott, D-Wash., illegally
leaked information to reporters. Why do Boehner and Gingrich think
this is different? Eckstein
</P>
<P>
   PENNSYLVANIA -- HUMAN. A human rights group in Washington
delivers a warning to Philadelphia and other cities trying to model
their police departments after New York City's aggressive,
zero-tolerance approach to even the smallest of crimes. In the
first four years of New York's aggressive community policing,
complaints of police abuse and excessive force shot up 56 percent,
a trend that could develop in any city without proper monitoring.
Kane
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS -- MEDICARE. Texas seniors may not be receiving all the
Medicare benefits they're eligible for, according to a report
released Tuesday by a health care consumer advocacy group. Brown
</P>
<P>
   -- MCALLEN. While many of the country's cities are enjoying an
economic boom, McAllen's is among the strongest, according to a
study released Tuesday. Marlin
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN -- FITCHBURG. While many of the nation's cities are
keeping pace with the country's economic boom, Fitchburg is one
city in which revenue growth -- though positive -- has lagged
behind. Marlin
</P>
<P>
   -30-
</P>
</TEXT>
