<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIVE-FRANK-PARTNER-BOS </SLUG>
  
 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story FRANK-PARTNER
(w, a) by Bob Hohler, which moved July 2, will wish to use the
following corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Because of a reporting error, the circumstances under which
Representative Barney Frank publicly disclosed his homosexuality in
1987 were mischaracterized in a Boston Globe story. Allegations
stemming from Frank's relationship with Steven Gobie, a male
prostitute, had yet to surface at the time of Frank's disclosure.
However, Frank later said he chose to acknowledge his homosexuality
partly because of his problematic relationship with Gobie, which
began in 1985 and ended several months after Frank's disclosure.
</P>
