<HEADLINE>
WINE TASTINGS: A STRONG MERLOT 
</HEADLINE>
  (bl) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Chateau St. Jean Merlot, Sonoma County, Calif., 1995. About $18.
</P>
<P>
   Chateau St. Jean made its reputation with a long series of
excellent chardonnays made by Dick Arrowood. There is a new
winemaker now, Steve Reeder, and while he is still producing fine
chardonnays, he might just make his name at St. Jean with red wines
like this 1995 merlot.
</P>
<P>
   Reeder is continuing the winery's practice of buying good grapes
from selected vineyards throughout Sonoma County. This wine is
composed of grapes from some of the best smaller appellations:
Alexander Valley, Knight's Valley, Sonoma Valley and Russian River
Valley.
</P>
<P>
   Both cabernet sauvignon and cabernet franc have been added for
structure. The wine spent 14 months in French and American oak, and
while it came in at a powerful 14.3 percent alcohol, it has a
velvety texture and a smooth, long finish.
</P>
</TEXT>
