<HEADLINE>
CULTURE NOTES: STARRING ON STAGE; ROMAN RUINS REOPEN; POETRY PRIZE
AWARDED; STAGE ROLE FOR MADONNA 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Ill.)  (lb) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Tony Danza will take over the role of Eddie Carbone
from Anthony LaPaglia in the Tony-winning revival of Arthur
Miller's ``View From the Bridge'' on July 21 ... Mary-Louise
Parker, last seen onstage in the Pulitzer Prize-winning ``How I
Learned to Drive,'' will star with Patricia Hodges and David
McCallum in ``Communicating Doors,'' a time-traveling comedy
thriller by Alan Ayckbourn, beginning previews on Aug. 5 at the
Variety Arts Theater ... The living legend Uta Hagen returns to the
stage on July 28 in Donald Margulies' ``Collected Stories'' at the
Lucille Lortel. The play concerns the relationship between a
brilliant writer and her young protege. ... For four weeks
beginning Wednesday night, Michael Cerveris will replace the
vacationing John Cameron Mitchell as the internationally ignored
song stylist Hedwig Schmidt in ``Hedwig and the Angry Inch'' at the
Jane Street Theater.
</P>
<P>
   Grand Reopening
</P>
<P>
   Nearly two decades after the ruins of the emperor Nero's lavish
Domus Aurea palace in the heart of Rome were closed for a
preservation project, the site will be reopened. Italy's Culture
Ministry says the palace will welcome visitors on June 25, 1999.
</P>
<P>
   When built, the palace occupied one-quarter of the city and
included a lake, several gardens and a residence so lavish that it
was dubbed the Domus Aurea, or Golden House. Since the early 1980s,
experts have been working to ensure that the palace, built by Nero
after the fire that devastated Rome in A.D. 64, is preserved from
the ravages of humidity and shifting earth.
</P>
<P>
   Metric Milestone
</P>
<P>
   W.S. Merwin, the poet, translator and environmental activist,
has been named the winner of the 1998 Ruth Lilly Poetry Prize,
which carries an award of $75,000.
</P>
<P>
   In announcing the honor, Joseph Parisi, editor of Poetry
magazine and chairman of the selection committee, said: ``In a
career spanning five decades, W.S. Merwin has become one of the
most widely read _ and imitated _ poets in America. His brilliant
work is the record of a spiritual quest for the authentic in the
self and in art.''
</P>
<P>
   Merwin will be honored by the Modern Poetry Association,
publisher of Poetry and sponsor of the Ruth Lilly Prize, in a
ceremony on July 28 at the Arts Club of Chicago.
</P>
<P>
   Cat's Meow
</P>
<P>
   Can Madonna fill the shoes of Barbara Bel Geddes, Kathleen
Turner, Kim Stanley and Elizabeth Taylor? Daily Variety reported
Tuesday that she is likely to make her London stage debut next
summer as Maggie in Tennessee Williams' ``Cat on a Hot Tin Roof.''
</P>
<P>
   According to Variety, the play will be directed by Peter Hall,
who staged the London premiere 40 years ago. Madonna last appeared
onstage in 1988 in the Broadway production of David Mamet's
``Speed-the-Plow.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-07-98 1739EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
