<HEADLINE>
LIBRARIES OF THE PRESIDENTS OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I recently visited the George Bush Library in College
Station, Texas, and found out that it is the 10th presidential
library. What are the other nine?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.S., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: There are actually 11, if the Nixon Presidential Materials
collection at the National Archives facility in College Park, Md.,
is included.
</P>
<P>
   The libraries contain the official documents of every president
since Herbert Hoover, whose facility is in West Branch, Iowa.
</P>
<P>
   The other libraries: Ronald Reagan in Simi Valley, Calif.; Jimmy
Carter in Atlanta, Ga.; Gerald Ford in Ann Arbor, Mich.; Lyndon
Baines Johnson in Austin; John F. Kennedy in Boston; Dwight D.
Eisenhower in Abilene, Kan.; Harry S Truman in Independence, Mo.;
and Franklin Delano Roosevelt in Hyde Park, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   These official presidential libraries are funded by the federal
government and maintained by the National Archives and Records
Administration. Some presidents have privately funded libraries,
such as the Richard Nixon Library in Yorba Linda, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Did Janine Turner have a child with Jerry Jones' son?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.M., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Mum's the word. Janine Turner is keeping the parentage of her
baby a private matter, according to publicist Leslie Kitay.
</P>
<P>
   On Nov. 22 of last year, Turner gave birth to her first child,
Juliette Lorraine Gauntt. The 35-year-old actor's real name is
Janine Gauntt.
</P>
<P>
   When Turner's pregnancy was first reported, several publications
quoted speculation by USA Today columnist Jeannie Williams that
Jerry Jones Jr. is the child's father.
</P>
<P>
   Although Turner lives in Colleyville, Texas, the best way to
contact her is in care of Creative Artists Agency, 9830 Wilshire
Blvd., Beverly Hills, Calif. 90212.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I went to school with Ed Harris here in New Jersey. Where can
I write to him today?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.P., Cliffside Park, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Harris in care of Mitchell Freedman, 15260 Ventura
Blvd., Suite 940, Sherman Oaks, Calif. 91403.
</P>
<P>
   Harris, 48, appears in at least two films this year: ``The
Truman Show'' and the upcoming ``Good Night Moon'' with Susan
Sarandon and Julia Roberts.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
