stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
July 8 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Joe Jares at the Daily News, (818) 713-3602.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
SOC-MODESTI-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ If ever soccer needed to impress
Americans, this was its chance. With the MLS lagging and support
for the sport sagging in the U.S., the World Cup promised to
showcase the world's game. Instead, Americans are still
underwhelmed with a sport that is mired by questionable officiating
and off-the-field shenanigans. &QL; 
By Kevin Modesti. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
