<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    22nd victim of E. coli tied to water park
 &HT;    By Diane Lore
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ A Fulton County, Ga. child has become the 22nd victim
of an E. coli outbreak linked to White Water park, public health
officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The child, who was not identified, visited the popular
Atlanta-area water park on June 11, according to Fran Buchanan, a
Georgia Department of Human Resources spokeswoman. The child did
not require hospitalization.
</P>
<P>
   Of those children who were hospitalized, a 4-year-old girl is
still listed in serious condition and a 2-year-old girl is in
critical condition at Scottish Rite Children's Medical Center, said
Kim Lathbury, a hospital spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
   At Egleston Children's Hospital, a 2-year-old boy continues to
be listed in good condition, according to hospital spokeswoman
Julie Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   No more tests that determine the genetic fingerprints of E. coli
O157:H7 have been completed, public health officials said. So far,
genetic tests are in on 11 cases and all are linked to White Water.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
