<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-07 22:30 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4592 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ALLSTAR-NOTES-COX     07-07 0480
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ALLSTAR-NOTES-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Beanie Babies the real star attraction at All-Star game
 &HT;    By I. J. Rosenberg
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ To heck with the All-Star paraphernalia Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Fans that came through the turnstiles at Coors Field wanted
Beanie Babies, a giveaway that got out of hand.
</P>
<P>
   Major league baseball decided to give away ``Glory,'' the red,
white and blue All-American Beanie Baby from the Ty Collection. It
was a gift from the owners and the players association, a gesture
the two had never done together before. Ty made only 100,000 pieces
with close to 60,000 being given away at the game.
</P>
<P>
   But numerous Beanie Baby addicts showed up outside the park to
try to buy them, and the negotiating began. They had signs telling
what they would give up for them. Some were offering as much as
$150.
</P>
<P>
   One buyer ran down a fan and said, ``Give you $75.''
</P>
<P>
   Said the seller, ``Oh, yeah, absolutely.''
</P>
<P>
   The players also received Beanie Babies, and one was overheard
to say, ``This is the best thing I can bring home.''
</P>
<P>
   Braves arms
</P>
<P>
   With Greg Maddux on the mound Tuesday, it marked the ninth start
for a Braves pitcher in the midsummer classic, matching the
Cardinals, Phillies and Reds for third most of any team.
</P>
<P>
   It is the sixth start for a Braves pitcher in the last eight
years. Tom Glavine was on the mound in 1991 and '92, John Smoltz in
1996 and Maddux in 1994, '97 and this year.
</P>
<P>
   Warren Spahn had the starting assignment in 1949, '58 and '61.
Maddux is the 13th pitcher to start consecutive games.
</P>
<P>
   All-Star bits
</P>
<P>
   David Wells became the first pitcher to throw a perfect game and
start an All-Star Game in the same season. ... Is there a true
rivalry between the leagues when it comes to the All-Star Game?
``It's fun, and that is really the way you approach it,'' said
11-time All-Star Frank Robinson. ``You enjoy meeting players from
the other league, talking and joking with them. Then when the game
starts, you get serious.'' ... Jay Leno-imitator Arsenio Hall was
doing interviews for the Tonight Show and put a container in Kenny
Lofton's locker labeled ``Viagra.'' It got a laugh from everyone,
even the cranky Lofton. ... Through the break, major-league
attendance is up 2.8 percent over last year at this time. ... The
media and players continue to pull farther and farther fapart.
Seattle's Ken Griffey Jr., a late addition to the home run derby
after the fans booed him in batting practice, took a shot at Rocky
Mountain News columnist Bob Kravitz: ``Now I'm a spoiled brat, a
punk, and I don't think I deserve that. I'm a villain. All because
of what some guy in Denver wrote about me.'' ... This is the first
year a city has hosted an All-Star Game and won a Super Bowl in the
same calender year.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
